value.value: A category of psychiatric disorders which are characterized by a disruption in the usually integrated functions of consciousness, memory, identity, and/or perception of the environment.

A category of psychiatric disorders which are characterized by physical or psychological symptoms that are intentionally produced in order to assume the sick role; there is no external incentive for the behavior, such as economic gain or avoiding legal responsibility, and the person is unaware of any self-motivating factors.

label.value: Mental Disorder Due to a General Medical Condition

value.value: A category of psychiatric disorders which are the direct physiologic consequence of a general medical condition.

A nucleoside consisting of uracil and D-ribose and a component of RNA.  Uridine has been studied as a rescue agent to reduce the toxicities associated with 5-fluorouracil (5-FU), thereby allowing the administration of higher doses of 5-FU in chemotherapy regimens. (NCI04)

label.value: Stage III Renal Cell Cancer AJCC v6

value.value: Stage III includes: (T1, N1, M0); (T2, N1, M0); (T3, N0, M0); (T3, N1, M0); (T3a, N0, M0); (T3a, N1, M0); (T3b, N0, M0); (T3b, N1, M0); (T3c, N0, M0); (T3c, N1, M0). T3: Tumor extends into major veins or invades adrenal gland or perinephric tissues but not beyond Gerota's fascia.  T3a: Tumor directly invades adrenal gland or perirenal and/or renal sinus fat but not beyond Gerota's fascia.  T3b: Tumor grossly extends into the renal vein or its segmental (muscle containing) branches, or vena cava below the diaphragm.  T3c: Tumor grossly extends into the vena cava above the diaphragm or invades the wall of the vena cava.  N0: No regional lymph node metastases.  N1: Metastasis in a single regional lymph node. M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 6th Ed.)
A category of psychiatric disorders which have as their most predominant feature a disturbance in mood.
A category of psychiatric disorders characterized by the presence of psychotic symptoms such as delusions or hallucinations or negative symptoms such as affective flattening.
A category of psychiatric disorders characterized by a disturbance in sexual desire and in the psychophysiological changes that make up the sexual response cycle.
A category of psychiatric disorders which include disorders related to the taking of a drug of abuse (including alcohol, prescribed medications and recreational drugs).
A six point scale that qualifies a person's physical abilities following a cerebrovascular accident. It is commonly used as a primary endpoint in stroke treatment studies.

A neuropsychological test of visual attention and task switching that requires a subject to connect a sequence of 25 consecutive targets. It provides an easy to administer and reliable assessment of attention, sequencing, cognition, visual search, and motor function.

label.value: Short Limb Dwarfism-Saddle Nose-Spinal Alterations-Metaphyseal Striation Syndrome

value.value: A rare genetic disorder characterized by bone marrow failure, spinal abnormalities, saddle nose, and metaphysical striation.
The extent of organ/tissue involvement by a malignant neoplasm is not reported or not assessed.
The space of the abdominal and pelvic cavities outside the peritoneum.
The point at which a line or curve crosses an axis.

label.value: Recurrent Childhood Malignant Germ Cell Tumor

value.value: The reemergence of a malignant germ cell tumor in children after a period of remission.
To establish something relative to a new reference scale.
A sympathetic ganglion located at the seventh cervical vertebral level.
A sympathetic ganglion located at the sixth cervical vertebral level.
A sympathetic ganglion located approximately at the first and second cervical vertebral levels.
A tissue sample that contains the trigeminal ganglion and branches of the trigeminal nerve.
A tissue sample that contains the submandibular and sublingual salivary glands.
A tissue sample that contains a seminal vesicle and coagulating gland.
A tissue sample that contains the rectum and anus.
A sample that contains lung and bronchial tissues.

A familial carcinoma inherited in an autosomal dominant trait.  It is characterized by the development of multiple, bilateral papillary renal cell carcinomas.  The carcinomas range from microscopic lesions to clinically symptomatic tumors.  It is associated with activating mutations of the MET oncogene.
An axillary lymph node along the brachial vein.
A lymph node along the left gastric artery or greater omentum.
A data imputation technique which populates missing values with the best possible outcome.

label.value: Best Observation Carried Forward Imputation Technique

value.value: A data imputation technique which populates missing values with the best-case nonmissing value.

An electrocardiographic finding in which there are two R waves, which are two deflections above the baseline resulting from a single ventricular depolarization. The first upward deflection in the complex is the R wave. The S is the first downward deflection. A second upward deflection is called the R-prime wave.

An electrocardiographic finding in which the QT interval corrected for heart rate using Bazett's formula is slightly prolonged. Thresholds for different age, gender, and patient populations exist. (CDISC)

An electrocardiographic finding in which the QT interval corrected for heart rate using Fridericia's formula is slightly prolonged. Thresholds for different age, gender, and patient populations exist. (CDISC)

label.value: Left Ventricular Conduction Delay by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding in which there is evidence that electrical transmission through the left ventricle is impaired. (CDISC)
An electrocardiographic finding in which both the atrial and ventricular rhythm are controlled by an electrical impulse from an artificial cardiac pacemaker. (CDISC)
An electrocardiographic finding in which the atrial rhythm is controlled by an electrical impulse from an artificial cardiac pacemaker. (CDISC)
An electrocardiographic finding in which the ventricular rhythm is controlled by an electrical impulse from an artificial cardiac pacemaker. (CDISC)

label.value: Right Ventricular Conduction Delay by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding in which there is evidence that electrical transmission through the right ventricle is impaired with a maximal QRS duration of 110 ms and which does not meet the criteria for Incomplete Right Bundle Branch Block. (CDISC)
The determination of the amount of Sjogren's SS-A antibody present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of Sjogren's SS-B antibody present in a sample.
Examination of a biological specimen to detect the presence of any protozoan belonging to the Trichomonas genus.
Examination of a biological specimen to detect the presence of any yeast cells that are in the long, filamentous and branching phase of growth.
An acute or chronic inflammatory process affecting the esophageal wall.
The determination of the ratio of total protein compared to the osmolality a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

A measurement of the amount of interferon gamma that is released when Mycobacterium tuberculosis antigen is incubated with a biological specimen, usually blood. Increased amount of interferon gamma suggests a prior or existing M. tuberculosis infection.
